result.formatted_address: Shop 307, 63 Nathan Rd, Tsim Sha Tsui, Hong Kong
result.name: Carpaccio

reviews.text:
Very disappointed with our experience at Carpaccio. We were lured in by the manager who was very friendly but things went downhill from there... 62 dollars for a warm bottle of water and the pizzas were really not of the quality you'd expect from an "Italian" restaurant. One of them definitely had not 
 been made fresh and had just been reheated and served. Not acceptable for 160 dollar per pizza.

First time there for a fathers day lunch. Cautious at first as restaurant was empty. But slowly filled up and as the food came out, it got better and better. Very friendly service, as long as you can get their attention 😉 amazing meatballs, crusted tuna and home-made pasta. Definitely coming back.

Previous reviewers must be really kind to give 3 stars. Overall the taste of the pizza and pasta were really bland and flat. You can barely taste the cheese and tomato from the pizza. It's a sham to call this an Italian restaurant. Go eat Motorino or Paizano if you want a true Italian pizza experience.

Simply, not bad but overpriced for quality and flavor. The staffs are good. The manager needs to have more attention to what they're serving instead of showing "selective" intimacy and dancing in the restaurant. I admire for his passion. However, I believe it's time to raise the quality; or lower the price.
The calamari for starter, the batter was so thick.
The caesar salad with prawn(+40hkd) was decent, but small portion. 
I was surprised that the pizza was like my homemade pizza; I always make a soggy bottom pizza.
The carbonara was good.
Lovely place nice food exceptional staff

reviews.text: Isquare  Is a nice shopping mall it has really call art work in front of it. It's really busy has a lot of nice shops that are all open past 10:00 p.m. It's in a convenient location from the Subway. Has some good restaurants in it. And the movie theater

It's a modern and great design shopping center and close to my hotel. I went here for a lunch and found Mark & Spencer on the ground floor and shopped a bit here. Overall, it's a nice shopping center.
Good for shopping (M&S clothing and food hall, marketplace), kids-r-us and other kid brands, very good cinema, linked to TST MTR train station
Visited the EyeLounge.  Very nice location with breath taking views of the city! Good drinks and very nice restaurant and cuisine.
High end shopping mall in Kowloon. Big brands.
